===Councillors===
The SNP had 425 [[councillor]]s in [[local government in Scotland|Local Government]] elected from the [[Scottish local elections, 2012]]. However, since the election in 2012, 5 SNP councilors in Argyll and Bute have since left the party: Roddy McCuish, Mary Jean Devon, Robert MacIntyre,Michael Breslin, and Fred Hall, who all now sit as independents.

